        "type": "message",
        "text": "A couple things I always try to keep in mind as an editor:\n• Providing context \/ rationalization for my edits (per some of the comments above, that can be pointing to a style guide rule, brand messaging, data, etc.) That takes the personal nature out of it and adds objectivity. \n• If I can't even easily articulate _why_ I'm making an edit, I like to pause and reflect on if I'm making a change just for the sake of it, or to serve my own preference. ",
